To start Bagbot inside a tmux session (so it keeps running after you close the terminal):

```bash
tmux new -s bagbot
```

Then inside the tmux window:

```bash
cd ~/Desktop/TravisBot/bagbot
source ~/.bagbotvirtualenv/bin/activate
python3 bagbot.py
```

You’ll see the usual startup screen; press **Y** to proceed.

To leave it running but close your terminal:

```
Ctrl-b  then  d
```

To re-open the session later:

```bash
tmux attach -t bagbot
```

If you ever want to stop it entirely:

```bash
tmux kill-session -t bagbot
```

